## 1. Before You Start — Pre-Flight Checklist

### 1.1 Check Your Host Machine

Your physical Windows PC is the **host**. The VM runs inside it. You need:

| Requirement | Minimum | How to check |
|---|---|---|
| Windows edition | Pro, Enterprise, or Education (NOT Home) | Start → Settings → System → About → "Windows specification" |
| RAM | 16 GB recommended (8 GB absolute minimum) | Task Manager → Performance → Memory |
| Free disk space | 60 GB | File Explorer → This PC |
| CPU virtualisation | Enabled in BIOS/UEFI | Task Manager → Performance → CPU → "Virtualization: Enabled" |
| TPM on host | Not required (VM has its own vTPM) | Not needed |

> **If your edition is Windows Home:** Hyper-V is not available. You have two options: (a) upgrade the licence, or (b) use VMware Workstation Pro (now free) which also supports vTPM. The steps below use Hyper-V; notes for VMware differences are included where relevant.

### 1.2 Check and Enable Hyper-V

**Run this in PowerShell as Administrator on your host machine:**

```powershell
# Check if Hyper-V is already installed
Get-WindowsOptionalFeature -Online -FeatureName Microsoft-Hyper-V
```

Look at the **State** field in the output:
- `Enabled` → you are ready, skip the next command
- `Disabled` → run the command below

```powershell
# Enable Hyper-V (requires restart)
Enable-WindowsOptionalFeature -Online -FeatureName Microsoft-Hyper-V -All
```

After running this, Windows will ask you to restart. Do so.

**After restarting, verify Hyper-V Manager is present:**  
Start → search "Hyper-V Manager" → it should appear as an app.

📸 **SCREENSHOT:** `00-hyperv-manager-open.png` — Hyper-V Manager window open, showing your host machine name in the left panel.

### 1.3 Plan Your Timing

The M365 Business Premium trial is **30 days**. You should start the trial only when you are ready to run the lab from start to finish. Project 03 (Conditional Access) uses the same tenant, so plan both projects inside the same 30-day window.

**Recommended schedule:**
- Day 1: Phase 0 (downloads) + Phase 1 (trial setup) + Phase 2 (VM build)
- Day 2: Phase 3 (hardware hash) + Phase 4-7 (policies) + Phase 8 (app packaging)
- Day 3: Phase 9 (end-to-end test) + Phase 10 (evidence & documentation)

