## 2. Phase 0 — Tools & Downloads

Do all of this **before** starting the trial, so you are not burning trial days on downloads.

### 2.1 Download the Windows 11 ISO

1. Go to: https://www.microsoft.com/en-gb/software-download/windows11
2. Under **"Download Windows 11 Disk Image (ISO) for x64 devices"**, select **Windows 11 (multi-edition ISO for x64 devices)**
3. Choose language: **English (United Kingdom)**
4. Click **64-bit Download**
5. Save the ISO somewhere easy to find, e.g. `C:\ISOs\Win11.iso`

> The ISO is approximately 6.5 GB. Download it now on a good connection.

### 2.2 Download the Win32 Content Prep Tool

This tool packages `.exe` or `.msi` installers into the `.intunewin` format Intune requires.

1. Go to: https://github.com/microsoft/Microsoft-Win32-Content-Prep-Tool
2. Click **Releases** on the right side of the page
3. Download `IntuneWinAppUtil.exe` from the latest release
4. Save it to: `C:\Tools\IntuneWinAppUtil.exe` (create the `Tools` folder if needed)

### 2.3 Download 7-Zip (as the app you will deploy)

1. Go to: https://www.7-zip.org/download.html
2. Download the **64-bit Windows installer** — the file is named something like `7z2301-x64.exe`
3. Save it to: `C:\Tools\7zip\7z2301-x64.exe` (create the `7zip` subfolder)

> Do NOT install it on your host machine — you only need the installer file for packaging.

### 2.4 Install the Get-WindowsAutopilotInfo Script

**Run this in PowerShell as Administrator on your host machine:**

```powershell
# Step 1: Install the NuGet package provider (required to install scripts from PSGallery)
Install-PackageProvider -Name NuGet -MinimumVersion 2.8.5.201 -Force

# Step 2: Trust the PowerShell Gallery
Set-PSRepository -Name PSGallery -InstallationPolicy Trusted

# Step 3: Install the Autopilot info script
Install-Script -Name Get-WindowsAutopilotInfo -Force
```

**Verify the installation:**

```powershell
Get-Command Get-WindowsAutopilotInfo
```

Expected output: a line showing `Get-WindowsAutopilotInfo` with `Script` as the CommandType.

📸 **SCREENSHOT:** `00-autopilotinfo-installed.png` — PowerShell window showing the `Get-Command` output confirming the script is installed.

### 2.5 Install the Microsoft Graph PowerShell SDK (for Phase 3 online registration)

```powershell
# Install Microsoft Graph modules needed for Autopilot online registration
Install-Module -Name Microsoft.Graph.DeviceManagement.Enrollment -Force -AllowClobber
Install-Module -Name Microsoft.Graph.Authentication -Force -AllowClobber
```

This may take several minutes. Wait until the prompt returns.

