## 7. Phase 5 — Configure the Enrollment Status Page (ESP)

The ESP shows a progress screen to the user during device setup ("Setting up your device for work..."). It blocks the desktop until all required apps and policies are installed.

### 7.1 Navigate to ESP

In Intune: **Devices → Windows → Windows enrollment → Enrollment Status Page**

You will see a **Default** policy. Click on it to edit it, or click **Create** to make a new one.

Click **Create**.

### 7.2 Configure the ESP Policy

**Tab 1 — Basics:**
- Name: `TechCorp UK — Enrollment Status Page`
- Description: `ESP shown during Autopilot provisioning — blocks desktop until setup complete`

**Tab 2 — Settings:**

| Setting | Value | Why |
|---|---|---|
| Show app and profile configuration progress | **Yes** | This enables the ESP |
| Show error when installation takes longer than specified number of minutes | **Yes** |  |
| Time limit (minutes) | `60` | Allow up to 1 hour before showing an error |
| Allow users to collect logs | **Yes** | Critical for troubleshooting failures |
| Show custom message when an error occurs | **Yes** | Message: `Device setup encountered an issue. Please contact IT Support on ext. 2000.` |
| Block device use until all apps and profiles are installed | **Yes** | Forces complete setup before user gets desktop |
| Allow users to reset device if installation error occurs | **No** | IT should handle resets |
| Allow users to use device if installation error occurs | **No** | Do not allow bypass |
| Block device use until these required apps are installed if they are assigned to the user/device | **All** |  |

**Tab 3 — Assignments:**
- Include: **All devices** (or specifically `Autopilot-Devices` if you prefer)

**Tab 4 — Review + create:**
- Click **Create**

📸 **SCREENSHOT:** `05-esp-settings.png` — The ESP policy settings tab showing all configured values.

📸 **SCREENSHOT:** `05-esp-assignments.png` — The ESP policy assignments tab.

